{"nodes":[{"id":"docker_deployment_md","label":"Docker/Compose deployment: prerequisites, .env (DISCORD_TOKEN required; Spotify optional), volumes bot-logs/bot-stats/bot-cache, dashboard on :5000, resource limits, backup/restore, troubleshooting (FFmpeg, yt-dlp, DNS).","file_type":"markdown","source_file":"DOCKER_DEPLOYMENT.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"privacy_policy_md","label":"Privacy (2026-02-09): collects Discord user/guild/voice IDs, search queries, commands; uses data for playback, queue, autoplay recommendations (titles), permissions; claims mostly RAM/ephemeral; persistent listening history described as localized JSON (not user-behavior tracking); third parties Discord/YouTube/Spotify; no sale of data. NOTE: codebase also persists SQLite stats/settings (doc drift).","file_type":"markdown","source_file":"PRIVACY_POLICY.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"readme_md","label":"Product README: 2026 Pro Edition — gapless playback, SQLite via aiosqlite+WAL, uvloop, concurrency semaphores, smart search, per-server quality tiers, TTL cache; AI/autoplay/recommend features; Docker-first; web dashboard :5000 with metrics + remote command queue for owners; command tables for prefix/quality/stats.","file_type":"markdown","source_file":"README.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"terms_of_service_md","label":"Terms (2026-02-09): license for intended music use; prohibits illegal use, exploitation, spam/overload, ToS-violating streams; minimal IDs + local listening history titles for autoplay; claims no permanent DB (doc drift vs SQLite); as-is; third-party dependency disclaimer; termination right; contact developer.","file_type":"markdown","source_file":"TERMS_OF_SERVICE.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"landing_readme_md","label":"Landing page docs: static HTML/CSS marketing site; deploy via GitHub Pages/Vercel/Netlify/local; customization (gradients, bot name, OAuth invite URL); optional GA; UTM on invite links; support links.","file_type":"markdown","source_file":"landing-page/README.md","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"landing_robots_txt","label":"robots.txt: Allow all user-agents; sitemap URL points to Netlify-hosted sitemap.","file_type":"text","source_file":"landing-page/robots.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"requirements_txt","label":"Root Python deps: discord.py[voice], yt-dlp, ytmusicapi, aiohttp, uvloop, aiosqlite, cachetools, python-dotenv, google-genai (optional AI), spotipy, Flask+SocketIO+gevent stack, psutil, requests, pytest/black/flake8 dev.","file_type":"text","source_file":"requirements.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"music_web_app_requirements_txt","label":"Separate web app bundle: Flask 3, yt-dlp, ytmusicapi, gunicorn (lighter than root dashboard stack).","file_type":"text","source_file":"music_web_app/requirements.txt","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"tests_test_logic_py","label":"Async/unit tests: CircuitBreaker failure threshold, OPEN→HALF_OPEN recovery, CircuitBreakerOpen; AudioManager pending-resolution wait; queue index behavior after next_song + add_songs (regression for index increment). Exercises utils.circuit_breaker + audio.manager (not in chunk).","file_type":"python","source_file":"tests/test_logic.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"tests_test_performance_py","label":"Tests: RateLimiter sliding window; SongCache LRU+TTL eviction via cachetools (maxsize). Validates abuse/cache behavior tied to production utilities.","file_type":"python","source_file":"tests/test_performance.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"ui_views_py","label":"Discord UI: NowPlayingView (prev/play-pause/skip/stop/repeat/autoplay; avoids after_playing race on prev by stopping VC then play_current_song; 600s view timeout for memory); QueueView pagination; UIManager tracks per-guild messages, cleanup/delete, update_now_playing embed+tip, queue embed; uses config, logger, global audio_manager.","file_type":"python","source_file":"ui/views.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"ui_init_py","label":"UI package exports: NowPlayingView, QueueView, UIManager, ui_manager singleton.","file_type":"python","source_file":"ui/__init__.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_ai_brain_py","label":"Optional Gemini (google-genai): Hinglish persona short replies for play/skip/stop/errors/autoplay/join/leave; aio generate_content; 429/quota → static fallbacks; gated on config.google_api_key.","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/ai_brain.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_circuit_breaker_py","label":"Async circuit breaker (CLOSED/OPEN/HALF_OPEN): failure_threshold, recovery_timeout, call() wrapper, logging; decorator helper; global youtube_circuit_breaker for YouTube API path.","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/circuit_breaker.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_connection_pool_py","label":"YTDLPPool: asyncio.Semaphore caps concurrent yt-dlp extract_info; run_in_executor for blocking work; counters + get_stats success rate; global ytdlp_pool — prevents resource exhaustion / eases rate pressure.","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/connection_pool.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_db_py","label":"Async SQLite (aiosqlite): DB_PATH default /data/music_bot.db, WAL+NORMAL sync; guild_stats, command_usage, listening_history table, guild_settings (prefix, audio_quality); record_play upsert + history row; server/global stats queries; reset; one-time JSON migration from stats/ with sentinel .json_migrated. Cross-cutting persistence for analytics/settings.","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/db.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_limiter_py","label":"Sliding-window RateLimiter per user_id; warns on exceed; periodic cleanup when map large; preset play_limiter (5/min) and control_limiter (10/min) for command abuse prevention.","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/limiter.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_listening_history_py","label":"Per-guild JSON in autoplay_data/{guild}_history.json; HistoryEntry dataclass; async record_play/get_recent/get_last_played_url for recommendation context; max 20 tracks; separate from DB listening_history table (dual persistence concern).","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/listening_history.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_logger_py","label":"BotLogger: file handlers bot_errors.log/bot_info.log + console; structured info/error/warning/debug; helpers log_command_usage, log_audio_event, log_error_with_context — central observability hook used across UI and utils.","file_type":"python","source_file":"utils/logger.py","source_location":null,"source_url":null,"captured_at":null,"author":null,"contributor":null},{"id":"utils_stats_manager_py","label":"StatsManager facade: init runs db.init_db + migrate_from_json; record_song_play/command_usage 